170
00:24:39,200 --> 00:24:40,901
[SPEAKER_04]: This is a living wage definition.

171
00:24:43,003 --> 00:24:44,724
[SPEAKER_04]: We can go to the wage piece later.

172
00:24:45,164 --> 00:24:48,647
[SPEAKER_04]: That was replaced with a standard hourly wage rate definition.

173
00:24:50,442 --> 00:24:54,025
[SPEAKER_04]: In this first section, you can see applicability and exemptions.

174
00:24:56,226 --> 00:24:58,328
[SPEAKER_04]: And there was an addition of some waivers.

175
00:24:59,348 --> 00:25:16,880
[SPEAKER_04]: So there were exceptions for trainees who are part of a job training program, people who are working in a recognized supported employment program, employees who are exempt from federal or state minimum wage requirements, positions where housing is covered.

