00:28:06,433 --> 00:28:24,223
[SPEAKER_04]: for 50 weeks a year would equal but not less than 116% of the poverty threshold for a family of four, and that this would kind of go up with the CPI inflation measure or there would be a version 110% of the federal or state minimum wage, whichever is higher, or an inflation measure.

