[SPEAKER_06]: I think for wearing two different hats, I know the one hat is my academic hat for 30 some years I was.

269
00:37:45,928 --> 00:37:53,872
[SPEAKER_06]: Teaching at Northeastern where my specialties were state and local government law and state and local fiscal and tax policy.

270
00:37:55,673 --> 00:37:59,515
[SPEAKER_06]: Taught quite a number of the folks who are now at KP law.

271
00:37:59,535 --> 00:37:59,595
[SPEAKER_06]: And

272
00:38:03,088 --> 00:38:15,296
[SPEAKER_06]: spent a lot of time dealing with the legal issues of the powers of municipalities to regulate employment relationships and other regulatory matters.

273
00:38:16,216 --> 00:38:17,417
[SPEAKER_06]: The other hat is for

274
00:38:18,718 --> 00:38:37,972
[SPEAKER_06]: several years I was a selectman in your neighboring town of Lexington and dealt with some of these same issues from that perspective and I think have some familiarity with the challenges that you on the council face in dealing with an issue like this.

275
00:38:40,123 --> 00:38:45,424
[SPEAKER_06]: So let me just share a few quick thoughts.

276
00:38:45,805 --> 00:39:00,088
[SPEAKER_06]: And I think between Councilor Bears and Mr. Varanasi, you've gotten a clear view of the differences between the two versions of an ordinance that are before you.

277
00:39:00,148 --> 00:39:05,270
[SPEAKER_06]: I won't spend time on that, but I do wanna emphasize that

278
00:39:06,445 --> 00:39:17,926
[SPEAKER_06]: It has been increasingly common in Massachusetts, and it has often and always been common in many other states, for municipalities to see a need to add

279
00:39:18,889 --> 00:39:32,012
[SPEAKER_06]: protections and requirements for employment rights and contractor duties above and beyond those that are imposed by the state itself.

280
00:39:32,733 --> 00:39:44,676
[SPEAKER_06]: Sometimes modeled on things that the state has done or that other state agencies have done, but that have expanded the protections and rights available for

281
00:39:45,736 --> 00:39:52,518
[SPEAKER_06]: folks that work in and particularly folks who are paid through the municipality.

282
00:39:54,259 --> 00:40:01,421
[SPEAKER_06]: The type of ordinance that you are considering is by no means unique in Massachusetts.

283
00:40:03,242 --> 00:40:07,463
[SPEAKER_06]: Boston and Cambridge have both had ordinances that cover

284
00:40:07,963 --> 00:40:13,826
[SPEAKER_06]: at least some of the topics that the proposal before you covers for decades now.

285
