[SPEAKER_06]: These are quite well established.

286
00:40:16,847 --> 00:40:36,816
[SPEAKER_06]: The use of labor peace agreements is not as common at the municipal level, but it's very common in public contracting more widely and is a well-recognized

287
00:40:37,340 --> 00:40:53,411
[SPEAKER_06]: way of ensuring both the good of the community, the good of the contracting entity, because it ensures that their laborers will actually be doing the work, and it respects the rights and dignity of the workers themselves.

288
00:40:55,813 --> 00:40:57,394
[SPEAKER_06]: As a former municipal

289
00:41:00,488 --> 00:41:14,792
[SPEAKER_06]: legislator myself as a selectman in Lexington, I do understand the fiscal pressures that you are and every other municipality in Massachusetts are facing.

290
00:41:15,492 --> 00:41:26,995
[SPEAKER_06]: And I know that the argument for privatizing services, for finding less expensive ways to deliver services are potent and

291
